Peta Brady https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peta_Brady 0 Peta Brady (born 1972) is an Australian actress. She is best known for being the second actress to play Cody Willis, a role instituted by Amelia Frid in the TV soap opera Neighbours. Since she left the show, Brady has appeared in the film Mullet, the TV sitcom Kath Kim and the SBS series RAN (Remote Area Nurse). In a recent theatre role, Brady played 'Annie' in Love by Patricia Cornelius. At the 2005 Green Room Awards, Brady won the Gerda Nicholson Award for an Actress with an Emerging Career.
